ce:section.ce:para:
Attending to previous published work a mass of citric acid (m

                           CA
                        ) and a mass of urea (m

                           UR
                        ) of 1 g with the same synthesis conditions were used for all the CDs synthesis [35]. In these CDs synthesis, and beside 1 g of these two compounds, a different mass of sodium thiosulfate (m

                           ST
                        ) from 0.5 to 3 g was also used. For the CDs microwave synthesis a domestic microwave with a maximum radiation potency of 700 w was used. A volume of water of 15 mL, a microwave radiation potency of 700 w and a microwave time 5 min were used in all the synthesis. The synthesized CDs were leaving to cool, diluted with water and posterior centrifuged at 9000 rpm during 10 min in order to eliminated suspended impurities. A final of 30 mL were posterior set with water.
